result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant appeared with counsel Jon Sherman.  Melissa Inlow appeared for the State.  No victim impact statement or restitution request received by DA.  Victim was notified by DA.  Defendant pleads NC to count 1 in 15CM46.  Court reviews charges and plea agreement/plea questionnaire/waiver of rights with defendant.  Finds he freely, voluntarily, and intelligently makes his plea and waives his rights; factual basis exists.  Joint recommendation of 1 year probation with conditions.  Defendant speaks.  Court makes a finding of guilt and adopts the recommendation with the following probation conditions:  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants. Defendant may not possess or consume any alcohol, nor be anywhere alcohol is available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.  If agent deems AODA appropriate as a result of assessment the defendant must comply with any and all recommendations for counseling and/or treatment.  Must pay the costs of the action.  Count 2 in 15CM46 is dismissed and read-in.  15CM166 is dismissed and read-in.

Covers 15CM166, 15CM46.   Defendant shall not consume any alcohol unless a physician states in writing that the defendant is alcohol dependent and complete withdrawal could endanger the defendant's health or life. In this case a doctor's excuse must be submitted to the Jackson County Clerk of Court or the Jackson County Jail within 48 hours of the bond being signed. Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, bar areas of restaurants, or where available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.
